# lint-i18n allowlist — keys that the static scanner will see used in code
# but are intentionally NOT in en.json. One per line. Trailing `*` matches
# by prefix; no glob beyond that. Lines starting with `#` are comments.
#
# Categories:
#   • Server-supplied labels: reference data dropdowns (admin authors the
#     `code` field freely; labels render via terminology service, not i18n)
#   • Dynamic key construction: the scanner can't statically resolve
#     `translate.instant(`prefix.${variant}`)` calls
#   • Settings / system config keys: `app.name`, `jobs.*` — these are
#     persisted system_settings rows surfaced as labels, not i18n strings
#
# When adding an entry, leave a one-line comment explaining WHY so the next
# reviewer knows whether to remove it later.

# Server-supplied system_setting keys (rendered as labels in the admin
# settings page; not real i18n strings). Add prefixes here as we add
# settings.
app.*
jobs.auto_archive_days
jobs.default_priority
notifications.*
storage.*
ui.*
auth.*
mfa.*
billing.*
features.*
demo.*
integration.*
tenant.*

# Reference data group/code labels — admin-authored, surfaced via the
# terminology service, never present in i18n.
referenceData.*
terminology.*
